# collab/models.policy — governs which models the ClaudeCollab commands
# (/consult, /panel, /review, /delegate, /collaborate) may use. (/research is
# planned, not yet a command — see PLAN.md.)
#
# Format:  <tier>  <glob-pattern>        # optional comment
#   tier    = deny | ask | allow
#   pattern = a shell glob matched against the FULL provider/model id
#             (e.g. openai/gpt-5.6-sol, opencode/deepseek-v4-flash-free)
#
# FIRST MATCH WINS, top to bottom. Put specific rules above broad ones.
#   deny   — collab/ask.sh hard-refuses to run this model.
#   ask    — Claude must confirm with you before using it (ask.sh requires
#            COLLAB_CONFIRMED=1, which Claude sets only after asking).
#   allow  — use freely.
#
# Ships permissive (default-allow). Uncomment / edit to gate what YOU care about,
# or run `/configure-collab` for a guided setup. Personal prefs should go in a
# git-ignored `collab/models.policy.local` (ask.sh auto-prefers it) so they aren't
# committed; edit THIS file only to change the shared/committed default.
# Note: a bare `collab/ask.sh` with no -m uses opencode's default model, whose id
# isn't known here, so it can't be policed — pass -m to bring a model under policy.
#
# Examples (delete the leading '# ' to activate):
#   deny   *-sol*             # never use any Sol variant
#   ask    *fable*            # confirm before using Fable
#   ask    openai/gpt-5.6-*   # confirm before this whole family
#   allow  opencode/*         # free tier is always fine

allow  *                      # default: everything is allowed
